                 Though
he never appears in the novel, and though he may not actually exist,
Big Brother, the perceived ruler of Oceania, is an extremely important
figure. Everywhere Winston looks he sees posters of Big Brothers
face bearing the messageBIG BROTHER IS WATCHING YOU.Big
Brothers image is stamped on coins and broadcast on the unavoidable
telescreens; it haunts Winstons life and fills him with hatred
and fascination.